cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI

The paper uses deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, to extract features from satellite images of the built environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and regression modeling, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with health indicators and the impact of the built environment on obesity prevalence, which could fall under the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
